12typedef struct {

1327 * bus access.

1937/* Bitfield definition for register array: QCI_CNT */
1938/*
1939 * VALUE (RO)
1940 *
1941 * Filter counter (see 802.1Qci 8.6.5.1.1 f)
1942 * CNT0: Frames that matched filter
1943 * CNT1: Frames that passed gate
1944 * CNT2: Frames that did not pass gate
1945 * CNT3: Frames that passed Maximum-SDU size check
1946 * CNT4: Frames that did not pass size check
1947 * CNT5: Frames discarded by Flow Meter operation
1948 * Counters starting at value <0> after reset.
1949 */

1951#define TSW_QCI_CNT_VALUE_SHIFT (0U)

4291/* Bitfield definition for register: CPU_PORT_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_STRFWD */
4292/*
4293 * PORT (R/W)
4294 *
4295 * If selected port is set then the frame is transmitted in Store & Forward mode. This is necessary when the ingress rate of this port is slower than the egress rate of the transmitting port. In S&F, the ingress module is able to drop frames with bad CRC.bit 0 - CPU-Port,
4296 * bit 1 - Port 1, …
4297 */
4298#define TSW_CPU_PORT_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_STRFWD_PORT_MASK (0x1FFFFFFUL)

4309 * bit 1 - Port 1, …
4310 */

4990/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: MAC_MACADDR_H */
4991/*
4992 * PROMISC (R/W)
4993 *
4994 * 0 – disabled
4995 * 1 – enabled
4996 * If promiscuous mode is enabled, then reception of all frames independent from the
4997 * Ethernet destination address is enabled.
4998 * PROMISC can be changed at any time.
4999 */

5017/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: MAC_MAC_CTRL */
5018/*

5023 * FSTIM is write-locked if CSA=1.
5024 */
5025#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_FSTIM_MASK (0x1F000000UL)
5026#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_FSTIM_SHIFT (24U)
5027#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_FSTIM_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_FSTIM_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_FSTIM_MASK)

5029
5030/*
5031 * RCA (R)
5032 *
5033 * <ref_clk> active
5034 * 0 – not active
5035 * 1 – active
5036 * See chapter 11.2.3 for details.
5037 */
5038#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCA_MASK (0x100000UL)
5039#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCA_SHIFT (20U)
5040#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCA_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCA_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCA_SHIFT)
5041
5042/*
5043 * MCA (R)
5044 *
5045 * <mii_clk> active
5046 * 0 – not active
5047 * 1 – active
5048 * See chapter 11.2.3 for details.
5049 */
5050#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCA_MASK (0x80000UL)
5051#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCA_SHIFT (19U)
5052#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCA_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCA_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCA_SHIFT)
5053
5054/*
5055 * SEN (R/W)
5056 *
5057 * Safety Enable
5058 * 0 – disabled
5059 * 1 – enabled
5060 * If enabled, then two instances of the logic core of LLEMAC-1G are compared at
5061 * runtime to each other.
5062 * SEN can only be changed if RX_EN and TX_EN can be read as 0. Deactivation delays
5063 * of RX_EN and TX_EN have to be considered. It is possible to change SEN together
5064 * with the activation of RX_EN and TX_EN.
5065 */
5066#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_MASK (0x10000UL)
5067#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_SHIFT (16U)
5068#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_MASK)
5069#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_SEN_SHIFT)
5070
5071/*
5072 * CSA (R)
5073 *
5074 * Clock switching active (<tx_clk>)
5075 * 0 – not active
5076 * 1 – active
5077 * Switching of <tx_clk> is commanded if CLKSEL or FSTIM (see Table 11-1) are
5078 * written. Clock switching takes a few clock cycles and this is signaled with CSA=1.
5079 * When CSA=1 then CLKSEL and FSTIM are write-locked and cannot be changed.
5080 */
5081#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CSA_MASK (0x2000U)
5082#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CSA_SHIFT (13U)
5083#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CSA_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CSA_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CSA_SHIFT)
5084
5085/*
5086 * RCE (R/W)
5087 *
5088 * <ref_clk> enable
5089 * 0 – disabled
5090 * 1 – enabled
5091 * RCE can only be modified if CLKSEL=111. See Chapter 7.3.3 for further details.
5092 */
5093#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_MASK (0x1000U)
5094#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_SHIFT (12U)
5095#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_MASK)
5096#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RCE_SHIFT)
5097
5098/*
5099 * MCE (R/W)
5100 *
5101 * <mii_clk> enable
5102 * 0 – disabled
5103 * 1 – enabled
5104 * MCE can only be modified if CLKSEL=111. See Chapter 7.3.3 for further details.
5105 */
5106#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_MASK (0x800U)
5107#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_SHIFT (11U)
5108#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_MASK)
5109#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_MCE_SHIFT)
5110
5111/*
5112 * CLKSEL (R/W)
5113 *
5114 * TX path clock selector
5115 * 000 – <mii_clk>
5116 * 001 – <ref_clk> (recommended setting for this selection)
5117 * 010 – <ref_clk> divided by 5
5118 * 011 – <ref_clk> divided by 10
5119 * 100 – <ref_clk> divided by 50
5120 * 111 – <ref_clk> and enables modification of RCE and MCE
5121 * others – <ref_clk>
5122 * See Chapter 7 for further details.
5123 * CLKSEL is write-locked if CSA=1.
5124 */
5125#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_MASK (0x700U)
5126#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_SHIFT (8U)
5127#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_MASK)
5128#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_CLKSEL_SHIFT)
5129
5130/*
5131 * PHYSEL (R/W)
5132 *
5133 * Selection of the PHY (See Chapter 4.6.)
5134 * 00 – MII
5135 * 01 – GMII
5136 * 10 – RGMII
5137 * 11 – reserved
5138 * PHYSEL can only be changed if RX_EN=0 and TX_EN=0. Deactivation delays of
5139 * RX_EN and TX_EN have to be considered. PHYSEL can only be changed, if these
5140 * register bits can be read as 0. It is possible to change PHYSEL together with the
5141 * activation of RX_EN and TX_EN.
5142 * PHYSEL drives the output <rx_physel>.
5143 */
5144#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_MASK (0x60U)
5145#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_SHIFT (5U)
5146#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_MASK)
5147#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_PHYSEL_SHIFT)
5148
5149/*
5150 * GMIIMODE (R/W)
5151 *
5152 * GMII mode / Ethernet speed selection (See Chapter 4.5.)
5153 * 0 – MII: 10Mbit/s or 100Mbit/s
5154 * 1 – GMII: 1GBit/s
5155 * GMIIMODE can only be changed if RX_EN=0 and TX_EN=0. Deactivation delays of
5156 * RX_EN and TX_EN have to be considered. GMIIMODE can only be changed, if these
5157 * register bits can be read as 0. It is possible to change GMIIMODE together with the
5158 * activation of RX_EN and TX_EN.
5159 * GMIIMODE drives the outputs <tx_gmiimode> and <rx_gmiimode>.
5160 */
5161#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_MASK (0x10U)
5162#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_SHIFT (4U)
5163#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_MASK)
5164#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_GMIIMODE_SHIFT)
5165
5166/*
5167 * JUMBO (R/W)
5168 *
5169 * Jumbo frame support
5170 * 0 – jumbo frames not supported
5171 * 1 – jumbo frame supported (not recommended)
5172 * Jumbo frames are non-standard Ethernet frames with a size bigger than envelope
5173 * frames (which contain 1982 payload bytes). If jumbo frames are not supported, then
5174 * LLEMAC-1G generates the appropriate error signals (<tx_gmii_er> for the TX path
5175 * and <rx_avst_err> for the RX path).
5176 * Although jumbo frames typically contain up to 9000 bytes, the LLEMAC-1G can handle
5177 * an infinite frame size. The problem of jumbo frames is the necessary storage space in
5178 * transmission and reception buffers. LLEMAC-1G does not include storage buffers.
5179 * JUMBO can be activated or deactivated at any time. The new setting becomes valid
5180 * immediately after clock domain crossing.
5181 */
5182#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_MASK (0x8U)
5183#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_SHIFT (3U)
5184#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_MASK)
5185#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_JUMBO_SHIFT)
5186
5187/*
5188 * TX_EN (R/W)
5189 *
5190 * TX path enable
5191 * 0 – transmission disabled - Avalon-ST READY for the TX path will be set to 0.
5192 * 1 – transmission enabled
5193 * TX_EN can be activated or deactivated at any time. Deactivation may take some time.
5194 * If during deactivation there is a frame in transmission, then this frame will be
5195 * completed fist. Afterwards bit TX_EN can be read as 0.
5196 * After the transmission is disabled there may be pending frames left, waiting at the TX
5197 * stream interface.
5198 */
5199#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_MASK (0x4U)
5200#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_SHIFT (2U)
5201#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_MASK)
5202#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_TX_EN_SHIFT)
5203
5204/*
5205 * RX_EN (R/W)
5206 *
5207 * RX path enable
5208 * 0 – reception disabled – no frames fed to Avalon-ST RX path
5209 * 1 – reception enabled
5210 * RX_EN can be activated or deactivated at any time. Deactivation may take some time.
5211 * If during deactivation there is a frame in reception, then this frame will be completed
5212 * first. Afterwards bit RX_EN can be read as 0.
5213 */
5214#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_MASK (0x2U)
5215#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_SHIFT (1U)
5216#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_MASK)
5217#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RX_EN_SHIFT)
5218
5219/*
5220 * RESSTAT (R/W)
5221 *
5222 * Software reset of the statistic counters (see Table 3-8)
5223 * 0 – no reset
5224 * 1 – reset active
5225 * RESSTAT will be automatically set to 0 after the counters have been reset
5226 */
5227#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RESSTAT_MASK (0x1U)
5228#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MAC_CTRL_RESSTAT_SHIFT (0U)

5341
5342/*
5343 * INIT (R/W)
5344 *
5345 * INIT=1 results in a MDIO write/read transfer if READY=1. If READY=0 while a
5346 * transfer is already pending or if ENABLE=0 then settings INIT=1 has no effect and
5347 * the current transaction is withdrawn.
5348 */
5349#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_MASK (0x100U)
5350#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_SHIFT (8U)
5351#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_MASK)
5352#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_INIT_SHIFT)
5353
5354/*
5355 * READY (R)
5356 *
5357 * READY=1 indicates a finished transfer and also shows that the controller is ready for a
5358 * new transfer. READY=1 is only possible if ENABLE=1.
5359 * If READY=1 is signaled after a read transfer, then RD_DATA is valid until a new
5360 * transfer is started.
5361 */
5362#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_READY_MASK (0x1U)
5363#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_READY_SHIFT (0U)
5364#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_READY_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_READY_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_CTRL_READY_SHIFT)
5365
5366/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: MAC_MDIO_RD_DATA */
5367/*
5368 * RD_DATA (R)
5369 *
5370 * Read Data is available if READY=1 after a transfer has been started. RD_DATA represents the content of the management data field of the read transfer.
5371 */
5372#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_RD_DATA_RD_DATA_MASK (0xFFFFU)
5373#define TSW_TSNPORT_MAC_MAC_MDIO_RD_DATA_RD_DATA_SHIFT (0U)

5771 */
5772#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_TX_DONE_DONE_MASK (0xFFU)
5773#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_TX_DONE_DONE_SHIFT (0U)

5780 *

5788/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: TSYN_PTP_RX_STS */

5790 * OV (R/WC)
5791 *
5792 * FIFO overflow flag. PTP frame has been received and there was no free buffer available. Data has been lost.
5793 */
5794#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_OV_MASK (0x80000000UL)
5795#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_OV_SHIFT (31U)

5798
5799/*
5800 * AV_NXT (R/W)
5801 *
5802 * Read access: buffer data available – reading data from RX_BUF is valid.
5803 * Write access: switch to next RX buffer – shall only be done when buffer not empty (AV=1). Use field RX_SEL as indication when rx buffer switch has been done.
5804 */
5805#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_AV_NXT_MASK (0x40000000UL)
5806#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_AV_NXT_SHIFT (30U)

5808#define TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_AV_NXT_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_AV_NXT_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_TSYN_PTP_RX_STS_AV_NXT_SHIFT)
5809
5810/*
5811 * RX_SEL (RO)
5812 *
5813 * Current selected RX buffer for reading (0-7). Can be used to determine when RX buffer has been switched after setting PTP_RX_STS.NXT

6748/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: TSN_EP_MMS_CTRL */
6749/*
6750 * STATSEL (R/W)
6751 *
6752 * MMS statistic counter selection, value can be read in register
6753 * MMS_STAT
6754 * <000>: Frame reassembly error counter (802.3br, 30.14.1.8)
6755 * <001>: Frames rejected due to wrong SMD (802.3br, 30.14.1.9)
6756 * <010>: Frame assembly ok counter (802.3br, 30.14.1.10)
6757 * <011>: Fragment rx counter (802.3br, 30.14.1.11)
6758 * <100>: Fragment tx counter (802.3br, 30.14.1.12)
6759 * <101>: Hold request counter (802.3br, 30.14.1.13)
6760 * otherwise: <0>
6761 */

6960/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: SW_CTRL_EGRESS_ECSR_QDROP */

7300
7301/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD */
7302/*
7303 * PORT (R/W)
7304 *
7305 * If selected port is set then the frame is transmitted in Store & Forward mode. This is necessary when the ingress rate of this port is slower than the egress rate of the transmitting port. In S&F, the ingress module is able to drop frames with bad CRC.bit 0 - CPU-Port,
7306 * bit 1 - Port 1, …
7307 */
7308#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_MASK (0x1FFFFFFUL)
7309#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_SHIFT (0U)
7310#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_SET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) << TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_SHIFT) & TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_MASK)
7311#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_GET(x) (((uint32_t)(x) & TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_MASK) >> TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_STRFWD_PORT_SHIFT)
7312
7313/* Bitfield definition for register of struct array TSNPORT: SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_PORTMASK */
7314/*
7315 * PORT (R/W)
7316 *
7317 * Port grouping via port mask. If the selected port is not set then the destination will be filtered out. This register allows the realization of port-based-VLAN (no VLAN tags required, only set it by ports).
7318 * bit 0 - CPU-Port,
7319 * bit 1 - Port 1, …
7320 */
7321#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_PORTMASK_PORT_MASK (0x1FFFFFFUL)
7322#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_PORTMASK_PORT_SHIFT (0U)

7328 * PORT (R/W)
7329 *
7330 * Mirror Port. If port mirroring is enabled TX/RX traffic will also be forwarded to this port.
7331 * bit 0 - CPU-Port,
7332 * bit 1 - Port 1, …
7333 */
7334#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_MIRROR_PORT_MASK (0x1FFFFFFUL)
7335#define TSW_TSNPORT_RXFIFO_SW_CTRL_IGRESS_RX_FDFIFO_E_MIRROR_PORT_SHIFT (0U)

7340/*
7341 * PORT (R/W)
7342 *
7343 * Mirror Selection TX. The destination of the frame is compared with this vector. All matching TX probe ports will be mirrored to MIRROR. It is necessary to configure all ingress ports to mirror the complete TX traffic.
7344 * bit 0 - CPU-Port,
